>>d362f993-7574-4ed3-be57-2e339f3ee6e1
Heads up, deleting the users.json means that you won't be using the same blacklist anymore. The blacklist.json is still on your machine, but it's saved in the directory of your previous cert. I wrote a simple bash script to move the blacklist from my current cert's user folder into the newly generated cert's folder. That way I don't have to re-blacklist boards every time I generate a new cert.
